{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You're assigned an academic mentor and possibly a workplace/industrial mentor during the work placement.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab You keep a logbook that's signed off on by your industrial mentor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Website lists companies, you can see job descriptions and work summaries\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Always ask for job descriptions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Some small companies may struggle with putting that together\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Work summaries are done by students who've been on placement describing their placement, including some advice for people.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Be open when looking at job descriptions \u8211- don't think that you can't do it, don't limit yourself\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Websites list interview schedules as well, and the results of the interviews.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Majority of recruitment is done around or before November. Interviews may be happening every day for the first few weeks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab CVs are sent out in the first week back in September. Important to get them prepped now.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Try to use placement as a means of travelling, e.g. to UK or EU.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab There's an option of a 12-month placement, which means you take your final year with another group.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab There's info on the website about organising your own placement.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Hard to get a placement in the States if you don't have your own visa.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Ask if the placement is paid at latest when you get the offer.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Shortlist, Interview & Selection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab CVs sent out in September 2017\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Employer shortlists students based on CVs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Interviews commence mid September 2017\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Interview schedule is on the placement website\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Feedback available\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You're given a list of companies, you select a minimum of 5-7 out of a potential 40 that you'd like to work with.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You have to be happy to go to any of those companies \u8211- you {\b have to take the first offer you're made}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Students from last year have said that they limited their choices too much on the list.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Interview feedback is available from most employers.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Interview results will be posted on the web. Successful students will always be called and put in touch with the company.\par}
