{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 CV\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Name, address, phone number\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Education 1st-3rd year subjects with 1st-2nd year results included\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Languages, operating systems, and applications you know\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Projects you have worked on since first year (individual and group)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Leaving Cert (or other) and include your results\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Work Experience - in reverse chronological order\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 7.\tx360\tab Hobbies, interests, and achievements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 8.\tx360\tab Referees - available on request\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Think ahead - what subjects will you be studying in 3rd year.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Appropriate to write first class honours for first year even though they're not awarded (if you got above 70%)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Mention weekly assignments in different modules under projects.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Now is a good time to volunteer if you've no work experience so far.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Bullet points and subheading clearer and easier to read fast\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Put self-taught stuff on the CV\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab College scholar things possibly worth putting on\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Have one academic referee that knows you.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Two page maximum.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Make sure your leaving cert results are correct on your CV.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Make sure {\b everything} is correct on your CV.\sa180\par}
